cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with cross-language plagiarism detection methods on a new dataset containing parallel and comparable collections of documents with different languages. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as plagiarism detection involves retrieving similar documents. Additionally, it may be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning and AI techniques are used for plagiarism detection. Finally, it may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as plagiarism detection is important for maintaining the integrity and security of documents.
